# 🤝 Contributing to DocuGuard

Thank you for your interest in contributing! Here's how to get involved.

---

## 🐛 Reporting Bugs

1. Check [Issues](../../issues) — it may already be reported
2. Open a new issue with:
   - **Title:** Short description
   - **Steps to reproduce:** Exact commands / actions
   - **Expected behavior:** What should happen
   - **Actual behavior:** What actually happens
   - **Environment:** OS, Python version, output of `pip list`

---

## 💡 Suggesting Features

Open an issue with tag `[Feature Request]` and describe:
- What you want added
- Why it would be useful
- Any implementation ideas

---

## 🔧 Making Code Changes

```bash
# 1. Fork the repo on GitHub

# 2. Clone your fork
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/DocuGuard.git
cd DocuGuard

# 3. Create a branch
git checkout -b feature/your-feature-name

# 4. Make changes

# 5. Run tests — all 26 must pass!
python -m pytest tests/ -v

# 6. Commit
git commit -m "✨ Add: description of your change"

# 7. Push
git push origin feature/your-feature-name

# 8. Open a Pull Request on GitHub
```

---

## 📋 Commit Message Format

```
✨ Add:    New feature
🐛 Fix:    Bug fix
📝 Docs:   Documentation
♻️  Refactor: Code cleanup (no behavior change)
✅ Test:   Adding or fixing tests
🔐 Security: Security improvement
```

---

## 🧪 Running Tests Before PR

```bash
pip install pytest
python -m pytest tests/ -v
# Must show: 26 passed
```

---

## 📜 Code Style

- Follow PEP 8
- Docstrings on all functions
- Type hints on function signatures
- Comments explaining cryptographic steps

---

## 👥 Code of Conduct

- Be respectful and constructive
- Focus on the code, not the person
- Welcome newcomers

By contributing, you agree your code will be licensed under the MIT License.
